# Preserve git notes across `git merge --squash`

## Context

`git merge --squash` doesn't fire git's post-rewrite hook, so `notes.rewriteRef` can't help. But when Claude Code runs the commands, our PostToolUse hook fires for both `git merge --squash` and the subsequent `git commit`. We can use this two-phase window to copy notes from the squashed source commits to the new squash merge commit.

This only works inside Claude Code sessions (where hooks fire). Plain terminal, GitHub UI, etc. won't trigger it.

## Approach: two-phase hook

**Phase 1 — `git merge --squash` detected:**
1. Read `.git/SQUASH_MSG` (git creates it after squash merge, contains full SHAs of squashed commits)
2. For each SHA, read its `refs/notes/claude-prompt-trail` note (if any)
3. Save found notes to `.git/claude-prompt-trail-squash-notes` temp file

**Phase 2 — `git commit` (existing flow):**
1. Normal prompt capture runs as before
2. After attaching the prompt note, check for the temp file
3. If found, read saved notes, append them under a `### Squashed Commit Prompts` section
4. Re-attach the combined note with `-f`
5. Delete the temp file

